"VectorFeatureExtractor.create_features()\nVectorFeatureExtractor.get_feature_names()\nrun_interactive_matching()\nPyDI.fusion package\nSubpackages\nPyDI.fusion.conflict_resolution package\nSubmodules\nPyDI.fusion.conflict_resolution.date module\nPyDI.fusion.conflict_resolution.general module\nPyDI.fusion.conflict_resolution.list module\nPyDI.fusion.conflict_resolution.numeric module\nPyDI.fusion.conflict_resolution.string module\nPyDI.fusion.conflict_resolution.utils module\nModule contents\nSubmodules\nPyDI.fusion.analysis module\nAttributeCoverageAnalyzer\nAttributeCoverageAnalyzer.export_analysis()\nAttributeCoverageAnalyzer.print_summary()\nanalyze_attribute_coverage()\nanalyze_conflicts_preview()\ncompare_dataset_schemas()\ndetect_attribute_conflicts()\nprint_conflict_preview()\nPyDI.fusion.base module\nAttributeValueFuser\nAttributeValueFuser.fuse()\nAttributeValueFuser.get_value()\nAttributeValueFuser.has_value()\nFusionContext\nFusionContext.attribute\nFusionContext.debug\nFusionContext.debug_emit\nFusionContext.group_id\nFusionContext.metadata\nFusionContext.source_datasets\nFusionContext.timestamp\nFusionResult\nFusionResult.confidence\nFusionResult.metadata\nFusionResult.rule_used\nFusionResult.sources\n\n-----\n\n(\npd.DataFrame\n)\ndf_right\n(\npd.DataFrame\n)\ncolumn\n(\nstr\n)\nid_column\n(\nstr\n)\ntokenizer\n(\nOptional\n[\nCallable\n[\n[\nstr\n]\n,\nList\n[\nstr\n]\n]\n]\n)\nbatch_size\n(\nint\n)\nmin_token_len\n(\nint\n)\noutput_dir\n(\nstr\n)\nngram_size\n(\nOptional\n[\nint\n]\n)\nngram_type\n(\nOptional\n[\nLiteral\n[\n'character'\n,\n'word'\n]\n]\n)\npreprocess\n(\nOptional\n[\nCallable\n[\n[\nstr\n]\n,\nstr\n]\n]\n)\nestimate_pairs\n(\n)\n[source]\n\uf0c1\nReturn type\n:\nint | None\nclass\nPyDI.entitymatching.\nVectorFeatureExtractor\n(\nembedding_model\n,\ncolumns\n,\ndistance_metrics\n=\nNone\n,\npooling_strategy\n=\n'concatenate'\n,\nlist_strategies\n=\nNone\n)\n[source]\n\uf0c1\nBases:\nobject\nExtract vector-based features using embeddings and distance metrics.\nThis class provides vector-based feature extraction using sentence transformers\nor other embedding models to create high-dimensional feature representations\nof text data.\nParameters\n:\nembedding_model\n(\nstr\nor\nobject\n) \u2013 Either a string name of a sentence transformer model (e.g., \u2018all-MiniLM-L6-v2\u2019)\nor a pre-loaded embedding model with an encode() method.\ncolumns\n(\nList\n[\nstr\n]\n) \u2013 List of column names to create embeddings for.\ndistance_metrics\n(\nList\n[\nstr\n]\n,\noptional\n\n-----\n\nDateComparator\nDateComparator.compare()\nNumericComparator\nNumericComparator.compare()\nStringComparator\nStringComparator.compare()\nPyDI.entitymatching.evaluation module\nEntityMatchingEvaluator\nEntityMatchingEvaluator.create_cluster_consistency_report()\nEntityMatchingEvaluator.create_cluster_size_distribution()\nEntityMatchingEvaluator.evaluate_blocking()\nEntityMatchingEvaluator.evaluate_blocking_batched()\nEntityMatchingEvaluator.evaluate_matching()\nEntityMatchingEvaluator.threshold_sweep()\nEntityMatchingEvaluator.write_cluster_details()\nEntityMatchingEvaluator.write_debug_results()\nEntityMatchingEvaluator.write_record_groups_by_consistency()\nPyDI.entitymatching.feature_extraction module\nFeatureExtractor\nFeatureExtractor.create_features()\nFeatureExtractor.get_feature_names()\nVectorFeatureExtractor\nVectorFeatureExtractor.create_features()\nVectorFeatureExtractor.get_feature_names()\nPyDI.entitymatching.llm_based module\nLLMBasedMatcher\nLLMBasedMatcher.match()\nPyDI.entitymatching.ml_based module\nMLBasedMatcher\nMLBasedMatcher.get_feature_importance()\nMLBasedMatcher.match()\nMLBasedMatcher.predict_pairs()\nPyDI.entitymatching.plm_based module\nPLMBasedMatcher\nPLMBasedMatcher.match()\n\n-----\n\nand a trained scikit-learn classifier. This design allows users to leverage\nthe full scikit-learn ecosystem (hyperparameter tuning, cross-validation,\nfeature selection, etc.) while maintaining PyDI's DataFrame-first approach.\nParameters\n----------\nfeature_extractor : FeatureExtractor or VectorFeatureExtractor\nFeature extraction component that converts entity pairs to feature vectors.\nExamples\n--------\n>>> from PyDI.entitymatching import MLBasedMatcher, FeatureExtractor\n>>> from PyDI.entitymatching.comparators import StringComparator\n>>> from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n>>>\n>>> # Create feature extractor\n>>> extractor = FeatureExtractor([\n...     StringComparator(\"title\", \"jaro_winkler\"),\n...     NumericComparator(\"year\", \"absolute_difference\")\n... ])\n>>>\n>>> # Prepare training data\n>>> train_features = extractor.create_features(df_left, df_right, train_pairs, train_labels)\n>>> X = train_features.drop(['label', 'id1', 'id2'], axis=1)\n>>> y = train_features['label']\n>>>\n>>> # Train classifier using full scikit-learn workflow\n>>> clf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100)\n>>> clf.fit(X, y)\n>>>\n>>> # Use trained classifier with matcher\n\n-----\n\n(\nFeatureExtractor\nor\nVectorFeatureExtractor\n) \u2013 Feature extraction component that converts entity pairs to feature vectors.\nExamples\n>>>\nfrom\nPyDI.entitymatching\nimport\nMLBasedMatcher\n,\nFeatureExtractor\n>>>\nfrom\nPyDI.entitymatching.comparators\nimport\nStringComparator\n>>>\nfrom\nsklearn.ensemble\nimport\nRandomForestClassifier\n>>>\n>>>\n# Create feature extractor\n>>>\nextractor\n=\nFeatureExtractor\n([\n...\nStringComparator\n(\n\"title\"\n,\n\"jaro_winkler\"\n),\n...\nNumericComparator\n(\n\"year\"\n,\n\"absolute_difference\"\n)\n...\n])\n>>>\n>>>\n# Prepare training data\n>>>\ntrain_features\n=\nextractor\n.\ncreate_features\n(\ndf_left\n,\ndf_right\n,\ntrain_pairs\n,\ntrain_labels\n)\n>>>\nX\n=\ntrain_features\n.\ndrop\n([\n'label'\n,\n'id1'\n,\n'id2'\n],\naxis\n=\n1\n)\n>>>\ny\n=\ntrain_features\n[\n'label'\n]\n>>>\n>>>\n# Train classifier using full scikit-learn workflow\n>>>\nclf\n=\nRandomForestClassifier\n(\nn_estimators\n=\n100\n)\n>>>\nclf\n.\nfit\n(\nX\n,\ny\n)\n>>>\n>>>\n# Use trained classifier with matcher\n>>>\nmatcher\n=\nMLBasedMatcher\n(\nextractor\n)\n>>>\nmatches\n=\nmatcher\n.\nmatch\n(\ndf_left\n,\ndf_right\n,\ncandidates\n,\nclf\n,\nthreshold\n=\n0.7\n)\nget_feature_importance\n(\ntrained_classifier\n,\nfeature_names\n=\nNone\n)\n[source]\n\uf0c1"